reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars nice way to keep drives all in one place and organized
reviews.reviewText: This has helped to gather all my drives and keep in one place.While I like that it has different sized slots if you will for the drives it can be difficult to place them in so I have to just be careful when taking out the padding and putting in one of my drives.I am not a huge fan of the plain black case simply because it gets mixed up with a couple others I have for other things so I put stickers on this so it is easier for me to spot and know which container it is.Also I have far too many SD cards to keep in this so I actually have another case I keep those in and this is just for the drives.Good strong zipper that seems like should last for years.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is a big case. Will probably protect your flash drives through a hurricane!
reviews.reviewText: If you are looking for the ultimate protection for your flash drives, this case is probably as close as you are going to get. The hard EVA case, the internal padding, this case could be picked up by a hurricane and travel for miles before crashing to earth again, and I suspect the flash drives inside will be just fine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This case keeps all my flash drives safe and secured. I have many flash drives and most of them are different sizes but this case is able to accommodate all sizes. Soft inside and hard exterior to protect from your belongings.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for organizing flash drives. Very useful.
reviews.reviewText: This is a very handy storage for flash drives. I own a lot of flash drives, and previously I had bought a flash drive storage pouch but it held it by elastic bands and pockets. The pouch doesn't have a lot of capacity and so I have a whole bunch of flash drives all inside a box. Sometimes it was hard to find a drive or if I left it somewhere to know that it wasn't in the box.This solves this problem and keeps all the flash drives neat and organized. It contains a foam piece with flash drive sizes cutout. You pull the foam pieces out and put in your flash drive. All of this inside a hard shell case.Obviously, the odd shaped flash drives don't fit. Secondly, the labels on the flash drives are not visible. I have some that I bought in a pack and are exactly the same and have to label to know what has what.The SD card storage was very tight and wouldn't fit with the transparent cases they come in. If you just want to store the SD cards without the clear storage cases, this would work well.Overall, great idea and execution. While my pouch now stores the odd shaped flash drives, this stores most of my flash drives in a very neat and organized way.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars A little short for my longer thumb drives
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice storage case for thumb drives and memory cards, but it's a little short for my longest thumb drives. I had to put them towards the back of the case to get it to close (it was still very tight, pushing on the top of the thumb drives). It's a little larger than I expected, but that's fine because it allows for a lot of memory to be stored in one place.Something you should be aware of is the smell. It has an extremely strong chemical smell when first removed from the plastic packaging. It's so strong it gave me a headache. I had to put it outside on my porch for a day to get the smell down. Once it sat outside, the smell was greatly reduced.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This storage case is about the best that you are going to get for storing flash media.
reviews.reviewText: With no standards in place for the design of USB flash drives, we can find them in every configuration you can think of. There are tiny drives just a little bigger than the USB connector, drives the shape of a pack of chewing gum, and everything in between. They have got to be the most difficult to organize type of modern computer storage media that I've ever encountered.This storage case is about the best that you are going to get for storing flash media. For some thinner drives, I needed to use a piece of cardboard to keep them to stay securely in the foam cutout. I also found a thin piece of foam that I cut into a rectangle. I use this to keep all the drives from hitting the SD cards and to keep them more secure in the cutouts. They probably should have included one with the case.The SD cards cannot be stored while inside those little plastic clamshell containers. Those will not fit in the pockets. MicroSD cards can be stored in the pockets, but I feel they might not be very secure and possibly fall out + get lost.
